to solar because we

00:36:20.310 --> 00:36:21.700
want to bring back the coal--

00:36:21.700 --> 00:36:22.651
coal is subsidized.

00:36:22.651 --> 00:36:23.400
Oil is subsidized.

00:36:23.400 --> 00:36:25.380
They're all subsidized
one way of the other,

00:36:25.380 --> 00:36:26.972
tax credits or otherwise.

00:36:26.972 --> 00:36:28.680
And if you just strip
it all off and say,

00:36:28.680 --> 00:36:30.221
we're going to be
economic creatures,

00:36:30.221 --> 00:36:32.700
let's go get the
right stuff done--

00:36:32.700 --> 00:36:34.650
and if you add the
cost of regulation,

00:36:34.650 --> 00:36:36.775
and you add the cost
of cleaning up things,

00:36:36.775 --> 00:36:41.010
or you add the perpetual
liabilities we create,

00:36:41.010 --> 00:36:43.290
renewables are going
to win hands down.

00:36:43.290 --> 00:36:46.311
So I think we keep pushing.

00:36:46.311 --> 00:36:47.310
