00:39:43.170 --> 00:39:47.820
We can still sell clear
cullet at a material recovery

00:39:47.820 --> 00:39:49.080
facility in the United States.

00:39:49.080 --> 00:39:53.160
Clear glass is still
economically recyclable.

00:39:53.160 --> 00:39:56.740
But the colored glass, which is
most of it, is not, et cetera.

00:39:56.740 --> 00:39:58.327
So there's mountains
of it around.

00:39:58.327 --> 00:39:59.910
So one of the things
to do immediately

00:39:59.910 --> 00:40:01.800
on that is to say,
what can we use it for,

00:40:01.800 --> 00:40:06.439
for example while we
transition from glass or are

00:40:06.439 --> 00:40:07.230
continue to use it.

00:40:07.230 --> 00:40:10.860
It's quite a lovely material
and quite optimized actually,

00:40:10.860 --> 00:40:12.000
in many respects.

00:40:12.000 --> 00:40:14.080
It's, we could be
making things with it.

00:40:14.080 --> 00:40:18.180
So I think we can have local
manufacturers in places

00:40:18.180 --> 00:40:20.360
making kitchen counters out
of it, whatever we want.

00:40:20.360 --> 00:40:23.380
There's plenty of things to
do with glass as an aggregate.

00:40:23.380 --> 00:40:26.280
So start to think of it as a
resource rather than a waste

00:40:26.280 --> 00:40:27.710
and then see what happens.

00:40:27.710 --> 00:40:30.210
Don't just say, I have to melt
it and turn into glass again.

00:40:30.210 --> 00:40:31.626
You can turn it
into other things.

00:40:31.626 --> 00:40:34.560
So that's one kind of element.

00:40:34.560 --> 00:40:36.990
The other is as we look
at these materials--

00:40:36.990 --> 00:40:39.450
I wrote an essay for the
science journal, Nature

00:40:39.450 --> 00:40:42.390
that they entitled,
"Carbon is not the Enemy,"

00:40:42.390 --> 00:40:46.050
and I was calling it a
new language for carbon.

00:40:46.050 --> 00:40:47.844
And the thing that
made me so sad--

00:40:47.844 --> 00:40:49.260
and this brings
us to the children

00:40:49.260 --> 00:40:50.640
who see this as obvious--

00:40:50.640 --> 00:40:54.690
is that at the TED Conference,
which is going on now--

00:40:54.690 --> 00:40:58.350
last year the prime minister
of Bhutan got up and said,

00:40:58.350 --> 00:41:01.140
we're going to be a
carbon-negative country,

00:41:01.140 --> 00:41:03.760
and that's good.

00:41:03.760 --> 00:41:07.050
And it broke my heart because
to be a carbon-negative country

00:41:07.050 --> 00:41:11.320
being a good, that means carbon
itself must be a negative.

00:41:11.320 --> 00:41:14.010
So you have a double negative
making it good, right?

00:41:14.010 --> 00:41:17.820
The problem is, less
and bad are not numbers.

00:41:17.820 --> 00:41:19.990
Less is a relationship
of numbers.

00:41:19.990 --> 00:41:21.300
Bad is human value.

00:41:21.300 --> 00:41:24.870
So you can't multiply less and
bad and get a positive result.

00:41:24.870 --> 00:41:27.240
It's bad by definition,
just less so.

00:41:27.240 --> 00:41:30.090
So the idea of
carbon-negative as a positive

00:41:30.090 --> 00:41:33.240
broke my heart, because
carbon is source of life.

00:41:33.240 --> 00:41:35.680
So really it's the
human behavior.

00:41:35.680 --> 00:41:37.230
So this new language--

00:41:37.230 --> 00:41:39.960
I basically said, what if
we treat carbon emissions

00:41:39.960 --> 00:41:42.300
in the atmosphere
today as a toxin,

00:41:42.300 --> 00:41:45.390
and then we call that
carbon negative behavior,

00:41:45.390 --> 00:41:47.640
and let's call the
carbon fugitive.

00:41:47.640 --> 00:41:50.340
Because the value of
a tool is put there

00:41:50.340 --> 00:41:54.180
by the user, and the
intention of the user.

00:41:54.180 --> 00:41:56.550
So a hammer in the
hands of a child

00:41:56.550 --> 00:41:59.740
is a toy, in the hands of
a carpenter is your house,

00:41:59.740 --> 00:42:03.570
and in the hands of a
maniac it's a weapon.

00:42:03.570 --> 00:42:05.640
So the hammer is innocent.

00:42:05.640 --> 00:42:06.870
So is carbon.

00:42:06.870 --> 00:42:10.710
So carbon, unnatural
carbon in the atmosphere,

00:42:10.710 --> 00:42:13.110
not good-- fugitive carbon.

00:42:13.110 --> 00:42:14.550
Then in the middle
of it all would

00:42:14.550 --> 00:42:16.500
be durable carbon--
a limestone mountain

00:42:16.500 --> 00:42:19.740
sitting calmly,
or plastics, which

00:42:19.740 --> 00:42:23.370
are carbon that are being
recycled across generations

00:42:23.370 --> 00:42:24.880
over and over again.

00:42:24.880 --> 00:42:26.860
That's a durable form of carbon.

00:42:26.860 --> 00:42:28.470
So we call that durable carbon.

00:42:28.470 --> 00:42:31.040
If we burn it for energy--

00:42:31.040 --> 00:42:33.840
fugitive, oops, nightmare,
carbon in the atmosphere.

00:42:33.840 --> 00:42:36.579
So do not call this
waste energy thing

00:42:36.579 --> 00:42:39.120
renewable power, which we do in
the United States by the way.

00:42:39.120 --> 00:42:41.280
The EPA characterizes
waste energy

00:42:41.280 --> 00:42:44.730
as renewable power,
which is insane.

00:42:44.730 --> 00:42:49.650
Then this ends up in
the oceans, and we now

00:42:49.650 --> 00:42:54.150
hear that by 2050 the amount
of plastic in the ocean

00:42:54.150 --> 00:42:55.645
will be equal to that of fish.

00:42:58.200 --> 00:43:00.780
How are we doing on statistical
significance, right?

00:43:00.780 --> 00:43:04.170
So that is durable
carbon getting fugitive

00:43:04.170 --> 00:43:05.380
into the ocean.

00:43:05.380 --> 00:43:07.109
Oops, right?

00:43:07.109 --> 00:43:09.150
So I'm working on a project
to try and figure out

00:43:09.150 --> 00:43:11.250
how we stop that flow.

00:43:11.250 --> 00:43:16.500
Then if you have carbon in
soil, you have living carbon.

00:43:16.500 --> 00:43:20.930
So fugitive carbon, durable
carbon, living carbon--

00:43:20.930 --> 00:43:24.660
and living carbon accrues more
carbon from the atmosphere.

00:43:24.660 --> 00:43:26.160
And so we can start
designing things

00:43:26.160 --> 00:43:31.800
that send carbon back to
soil, even polymers like this.

00:43:31.800 --> 00:43:35.060
And we can even design
these polymers to biodegrade

00:43:35.060 --> 00:43:37.620
and compost into soil.

00:43:37.620 --> 00:43:40.920
Because I see this
oil as ancient soil,

00:43:40.920 --> 00:43:42.410
they just added an s.

00:43:42.410 --> 00:43:42.910
Right.

00:43:42.910 --> 00:43:44.620
Add the "s" and go to soil.

00:43:44.620 --> 00:43:47.730
So put the "s" back so
we can use various things

00:43:47.730 --> 00:43:50.454
like [INAUDIBLE] and open
up the polymer chains

00:43:50.454 --> 00:43:51.870
and design these
things to go back

00:43:51.870 --> 00:43:54.810
to carbon, hydrogen, and oxygen,
and build soil with them too.

00:43:54.810 --> 00:43:57.760
So that whole thing
is a design system.

00:43:57.760 --> 00:44:00.954
So that's a long answer to
what to do about the glass.

